        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
The Intersection Of Us-
380 And Highway 222, or 8 miles northwest of Throckmorton, moving
northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Us-183 Near The Throckmorton-
Baylor County Line and The Intersection Of Us-380 And Highway 222.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
